:: Rejection target: the Fraenkel comprehension generator ranges over the
:: bare template type parameter T, which carries no sethood evidence. If the
:: body were accepted symbolically, the instantiation `para[set]` would
:: denote the Russell class ({ x where x is set : not x in x }), deriving a
:: contradiction. Bare type parameters have no sethood; only a bound with a
:: proved sethood property or a `such that` constraint can supply it
:: (doc/spec/en/18.templates.md, section 18.10.2;
:: doc/spec/en/13.term_expression.md, section 13.4.2;
:: doc/spec/en/07.modes.md, section 7.8.1).

definition
  let T be type;
  func ParaDef: para[T] -> set equals
    { x where x is T : not x in x };
end;
